<p>Consider example with Angular <code>$resource</code> and <code>SpringDataRestAdapter</code> from <code>angular-spring-data-rest</code>: </p>  <pre><code>var resource = $resource("url/:id", {id: '@id'}, {query: {method: 'GET', isArray: false}});  $scope.questionary.query({}, function callback(data) {     SpringDataRestAdapter.process(data).then(function (processedResponse) {     } }); </code></pre>  <p><code>SpringDataRestAdapter.process</code> has the same semantic as <code>callback</code>.</p>  <p>How to pass <code>SpringDataRestAdapter.process</code> instead of <code>callback</code> with chained <code>then</code> call?  </p>  <p><strong>UPDATED</strong></p>  <p>Rewrote question with real world example.</p>